Test ROMs live in this directory. None are committed — the integration
tests under tests/blargg_tests.rs and tests/nestest.rs *skip silently* if
their ROM is missing, so `cargo test` passes on a bare checkout and
tightens up as you drop ROMs in.

All ROMs listed here are freely distributed by their authors for emulator
testing. Originals: https://www.nesdev.org/wiki/Emulator_tests


─── Fetch them automatically ───────────────────────────────────────────

    scripts/fetch_test_roms.sh

Downloads every ROM listed below from christopherpow/nes-test-roms on
GitHub (a curated mirror of the nesdev-wiki links). Skips files already
present; pass -f to re-download.


─── nestest (Kevin Horton) ──────────────────────────────────────────────

Drives every official 6502 opcode; the gold standard for CPU regression.
  File:   nestest.nes
  Source: https://www.nesdev.org/wiki/Emulator_tests#NES_Test
  Also includes `nestest.log` — the cycle-exact reference trace, useful
  for manual diffing when a test fails.


─── Blargg: instr_test-v5 (CPU instruction behavior) ────────────────────

The all-in-one ROM:
  File:   official_only.nes     (exercises only official opcodes)

Or the 16 sub-tests from `rom_singles/`, which give sharper error output:
  01-basics.nes        05-zp_xy.nes       09-ind_y.nes       13-rts.nes
  02-implied.nes       06-absolute.nes    10-branches.nes    14-rti.nes
  03-immediate.nes     07-abs_xy.nes      11-stack.nes       15-brk.nes
  04-zero_page.nes     08-ind_x.nes       12-jmp_jsr.nes     16-special.nes

  Source: http://blargg.8bitalley.com/parodius/nes-tests/instr_test-v5.zip


─── Blargg: instr_timing ────────────────────────────────────────────────

Verifies cycle counts for every instruction + the 8 branch scenarios.
Supersedes the older `cpu_timing_test6` (which only drew results to the
PPU screen and can't be polled programmatically). Requires a working
APU length counter.
  Files:  1-instr_timing.nes, 2-branch_timing.nes
  Source: http://blargg.8bitalley.com/parodius/nes-tests/instr_timing.zip


─── Blargg: ppu_vbl_nmi ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

VBlank flag and NMI timing.
  File:   ppu_vbl_nmi.nes
  Source: http://blargg.8bitalley.com/parodius/nes-tests/ppu_vbl_nmi.zip


─── Blargg: sprite_hit_tests ────────────────────────────────────────────

Sprite-0 hit edge cases (critical given our recent v/t/x rewrite).
  File:   sprite_hit.nes        (either the all-in-one or copy a sub-test)
  Source: http://blargg.8bitalley.com/parodius/nes-tests/sprite_hit_tests_2005.10.05.zip


─── Blargg: oam_stress ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

OAM DMA / corruption stress test.
  File:   oam_stress.nes
  Source: http://blargg.8bitalley.com/parodius/nes-tests/oam_stress.zip


─── Blargg: apu_test ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

APU register behavior. Will fail loudly until we implement the APU.
  File:   apu_test.nes
  Source: http://blargg.8bitalley.com/parodius/nes-tests/apu_test.zip


─── Running ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  cargo test --release              # runs everything (skips missing ROMs)
  cargo test --release blargg       # just the Blargg suite
  cargo test --release nestest      # just nestest
  cargo test --release -- --nocapture   # see the [pass]/[skip] messages
